description:
welcome to this week’s womxn run the herd event! we are headed to madrona for our monthly field trip to enjoy some madison park miles — here’s what you can expect:

- quick name/pronoun/ice breaker circle
- a 6 mile no-drop run (with options to cut it shorter)
- a girl dinner themed friendsgiving (girl dinnersgiving?) potluck to follow the run
- lots of gratitude & good vibes

exact address for the event, carpooling, and the potluck sign up spreadsheet can be found on the #womxnruntheherd slack channel!! please come prepared with a headlamp, extra warm/dry layers, and some girl dinner to share!

*this event is open to women, trans, and non-binary people who are comfortable in a space that centers the experiences of women. our only rule is that nobody runs alone :) 

(we will be back to our regular routine of 6pm @ the brooks trailhead on monday, december 2nd)
title: womxn run the herd: girl dinner

description:
Welcome to the best Thanksgiving you will ever experience. It's Cowsgiving IV everybody!!!

Join us for a morning trail run at East Tiger. Note the later start than usual, as most people should have the day off of work. I know one thing I'm thankful for this Cowsgiving: federal holidays!

Routes:
13.3: https://www.strava.com/routes/3294447303330077496 
11.7: https://www.strava.com/routes/3294441629654471254
8.2: https://www.strava.com/routes/3294442445951042996
3.8: https://www.strava.com/routes/3294443869552304952

Following the run, we will be hosting a Thanksgiving hang (start whenever) and potluck (starting at 6:30pm) back in Seattle. Carpool thread and potluck address on slack!

Bring navigation, and DM us with any questions!
title: Thirsty Thursday: Cowsgiving IV
